    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Little Professor Syndrome</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rhoda L Auld letter on Lawrence Osborne's June 18 article notes striking similarity between Geroge Bernard Shaw's character Henry Higgins and that of Asperger's sufferers/</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was rereading George Bernard Shaw's ''Pygmalion'' and could not help noticing the striking similarity between the behavior of Shaw's Henry Higgins and that of the Asperger's sufferers. Not only is Higgins a gifted individual with what might justifiably be termed an ''obsessive interest'' in phonetics, but he is also socially inept in very much the ways Osborne describes.</p>
        <p>Rhoda L. Auld  Greenville, N.C.</p>
      </block>
